title: Campaigners celebrate court ruling to ‘decolonise’ Kampala
description: After a five-year campaign, landmarks and streets honouring British colonialists will be renamed to reflect Ugandan cultureCampaigners have welcomed a court ruling to remove British colonial monuments from Uganda’s capital, Kampala, and to rename streets that honour “crooks and historical figureheads”.In last week’s high court ruling, Justice Musa Ssekaana directed the city authorities to remove the names of British figures from streets, monuments and other landmarks. title: World Food Programme to close office in southern Africa after Trump aid cuts
description: UN food agency received half its budget from US last year and is accelerating merger plan as a result of funding cutsThe UN’s World Food Programme (WFP) is closing its southern Africa office in the wake of the Trump administration’s aid cuts.In a statement, a spokesperson said the office in Johannesburg would close and the WFP would consolidate its southern and east Africa operations into one regional office in Nairobi, Kenya.
